Almost all Vietnamese dynasties are named after the king's family name, unlike the Chinese dynasties, whose names are dictated by the dynasty founders and often used as the country's name.

The [[Hồng Bàng Dynasty]] was a dynasty of the ancient Vietnamese nation before recorded history. The [[Thục Dynasty|Thục]], [[Triệu Dynasty|Triệu]], Anterior Lý, [[Ngô Dynasty|Ngô]], [[Đinh Dynasty|Đinh]], [[Anterior Lê Dynasty|Anterior Lê]], [[Lý Dynasty|Lý]], [[Trần Dynasty|Trần]], [[Hồ Dynasty|Hồ]], [[Lê Dynasty|Lê]], [[Mạc Dynasty|Mạc]], [[Tây Sơn Dynasty|Tây Sơn]], and [[Nguyễn Dynasty|Nguyễn]] are usually regarded by historians as formal dynasties. Nguyễn Huệ's "Tây Sơn Dynasty" is rather a name created by historians to avoid confusion with Nguyễn Anh's Nguyễn Dynasty.

